HEADWORD: Conversable
<hw>Con*vers"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>conversable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Qualified for conversation; disposed
to converse; sociable; free in discourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While young, humane, <qex>conversable</qex>, and kind.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conversableness</ent>⟦br⟧
